		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Already ahead of you, except I'm working on a single board Famicom designed to fit back into a old model Famicom, no more 74 series (now a small CPLD, so it has a little propriety), 2k/8k selectable WRAM, thinking about a NTSC/PAL switchable design using a PAL encoder (PAL video with real 60hz gameplay ;) I have a cool Hong Kong Famicom that can do this but since I don't live in a PAL country, I dunno if I should bother. I thought it would be cool to use the CPLD to additionally put in a HW debugger, that's way too ambitious for me however

		

		</td>
	</tr>
